+ under the License.
+-->
+<document xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0"
+  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
+  xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/xdoc-2.0.xsd">
+  <properties>
+    <title>Project Site Deployment</title>
+    <author email="dev@commons.apache.org">Apache Commons Team</author>
+  </properties>
+  <body>
+    <section name="Overview">
+      <p>
+        This page describes how to build, validate and publish the Apache Commons CLI project site.
+        The site is generated with Maven Site and deployed to the Apache Commons web infrastructure
+        defined in the project <code>pom.xml</code>.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        Static SVG assets under <code>src/site/resources/images/svg</code> are deployed together with the rest of the site.
+        In particular, <code>diagrams-cli2.js</code> and <code>diagrams.css</code> are part of the published output used by
+        <a href="resources/images/svg/options.svg">options.svg</a> and
+        <a href="resources/images/svg/commandlines.svg">commandlines.svg</a>.
+      </p>
+    </section>
+
+    <section name="Prerequisites">
+      <ul>
+        <li>A JDK version compatible with the <code>maven.compiler.source</code> property in the project <code>pom.xml</code>.</li>
+        <li>Apache Maven installed and available on the command line.</li>
+        <li>Subversion command line tooling available as <code>svn</code>.</li>
+        <li>Apache committer credentials configured for the <code>apache.website</code> server entry in Maven settings.</li>
+      </ul>
+      <p>
+        On a fresh machine, the build automatically prepares a local <code>site-content</code> working copy before site publication.
+      </p>
+    </section>
+
+    <section name="Build and Validate Locally">
+      <p>Generate the site locally before publishing any change:</p>
+      <source>
+mvn clean site
+      </source>
+      <p>
+        Review the generated output in <code>target/site</code>. The deployment page generated from this source is
+        <code>target/site/deployment.html</code>.
+      </p>
+      <p>Validate the site-specific SVG assets as part of the review:</p>
+      <ul>
+        <li><code>target/site/resources/images/svg/options.svg</code></li>
+        <li><code>target/site/resources/images/svg/commandlines.svg</code></li>
+        <li><code>target/site/resources/images/svg/diagrams-cli2.js</code></li>
+        <li><code>target/site/resources/images/svg/diagrams.css</code></li>
+      </ul>
+      <p>
+        Open the generated SVG files directly in a browser when you want to confirm that the diagrams render with their script and stylesheet dependencies.
+      </p>
+    </section>
+
+    <section name="Publish the Project Site">
+      <p>
+        Commons CLI is a single-module project and publishes its site using the distribution management site URL configured in the project <code>pom.xml</code>.
+      </p>
+      <source>
+mvn site-deploy
+      </source>
+      <p>
+        The deployment target is the Apache Commons production site location for Commons CLI. During publication,
+        the local <code>site-content</code> checkout is updated and the generated site content is synchronized into it.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        The current configuration preserves previously published Javadocs by excluding <code>javadocs**</code> from automatic deletion.
+      </p>
+    </section>
+
+    <section name="Release Candidate Site">
+      <p>
+        To publish the release candidate site to the versioned staging location defined by the <code>rc</code> Maven profile, run:
+      </p>
+      <source>
+mvn -Prc site-deploy
+      </source>
+    </section>
+
+    <section name="Deployment Checklist">
+      <ul>
+        <li>Run <code>mvn clean site</code>.</li>
+        <li>Review <code>target/site/deployment.html</code> and the generated SVG assets.</li>
+        <li>Confirm that navigation includes the deployment page.</li>
+        <li>Run <code>mvn site-deploy</code> for production or <code>mvn -Prc site-deploy</code> for release candidate staging.</li>
+      </ul>
+    </section>
+  </body>
+</document>
